title_narrative: Humanitarian mine action in Somalia NL MFA 2020-2024
sector_narrative: This project aims to safe lives and increase livelihoods in Somalia by: 1) clearing landmines and other explosive items, 2) responding to EOD callouts, 3) conducting survey, 4) providing victim assistance, 4) providing risk education and 5) providing capacity building to the Somali Explosive Management Authority (SEMA).

This project aims to safe lives and increase livelihoods in Somalia by: 1) clearing landmines and other explosive items, 2) responding to EOD callouts, 3) conducting survey, 4) providing victim assistance, 4) providing risk education and 5) providing capacity building to the Somali Explosive Management Authority (SEMA).

This project aims to safe lives and increase livelihoods in Somalia by: 1) clearing landmines and other explosive items, 2) responding to EOD callouts, 3) conducting survey, 4) providing victim assistance, 4) providing risk education and 5) providing capacity building to the Somali Explosive Management Authority (SEMA).
description_narrative: This project aims to safe lives and increase livelihoods in Somalia by: 1) clearing landmines and other explosive items, 2) responding to EOD callouts, 3) conducting survey, 4) providing victim assistance, 4) providing risk education and 5) providing capacity building to the Somali Explosive Management Authority (SEMA).

This project aims to safe lives and increase livelihoods in Somalia by: 1) clearing landmines and other explosive items, 2) responding to EOD callouts, 3) conducting survey, 4) providing victim assistance, 4) providing risk education and 5) providing capacity building to the Somali Explosive Management Authority (SEMA).

The target groups for this project are communities suffering from the threat of landmines and other explosive remnants of war in Somalia. The target group for the capacity building is the Somali Explosive Management Authority (SEMA).
